to-the-tunnel","score":10,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"untitaker","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ios","networking"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2jqoor","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2jqoor/force_all_app_traffic_into_tunnel"},{"short_id":"hiawu3","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:59:05.000-05:00","title":"Pixel Bit-Depth Increase by Bit Replication (1998)","url":"https://cv.ulichney.com/papers/1998-bit-replication.pdf","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"pekkavaa","user_is_author":false,"tags":["graphics","math","pdf"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hiawu3","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hiawu3/pixel_bit_depth_increase_by_bit"},{"short_id":"6vx5uy","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:55:07.000-05:00","title":"Features everyone should steal from npmx","url":"https://nesbitt.io/2026/04/16/features-everyone-should-steal-from-npmx.html","score":17,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Jackevansevo","user_is_author":false,"tags":["javascript"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/6vx5uy","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/6vx5uy/features_everyone_should_steal_from_npmx"},{"short_id":"fgwvua","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:03:20.000-05:00","title":"Performance of the Wren programming language","url":"https://wren.io/performance.html","score":19,"flags":0,"comment_count":9,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"fanf","user_is_author":false,"tags":["plt"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fgwvua","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fgwvua/performance_wren_programming_language"},{"short_id":"cfzhwf","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:53:02.000-05:00","title":"How are you protecting yourself against the imminent AI dooms zero day?","url":"","score":10,"flags":2,"comment_count":24,"description":"\u003cp\u003eAbove all this is a fun discussion. Don't get too serious :)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs LLMs get better and better at pattern matching against vulnerabilities, and gaining better logical inference, it's a matter of time until a human or a group of humans and an LLM(s) find a plethora of zero days, some possibly unpatchable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI'm sure others have thought the same, so I'm curious just what the general zeitgeist is. I personally think any machine you haven't put online, like those 10 year old laptops in the closest, are safe. The problem is, \u003cem\u003eI believe airgap will not save us either\u003c/em\u003e if a truly advanced system is developed. More or less I think \"primitive technology\" could return in various ways depending what we're talking about, like in finance, to avoid manipulation.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Above all this is a fun discussion. Don't get too serious :)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAs LLMs get better and better at pattern matching against vulnerabilities, and gaining better logical inference, it's a matter of time until a human or a group of humans and an LLM(s) find a plethora of zero days, some possibly unpatchable.\r\n\r\nI'm sure others have thought the same, so I'm curious just what the general zeitgeist is. I personally think any machine you haven't put online, like those 10 year old laptops in the closest, are safe. The problem is, *I believe airgap will not save us either* if a truly advanced system is developed. More or less I think \"primitive technology\" could return in various ways depending what we're talking about, like in finance, to avoid manipulation.","submitter_user":"LenFalken","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ai","ask"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cfzhwf","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cfzhwf/how_are_you_protecting_yourself_against"},{"short_id":"ual4t5","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:48:53.000-05:00","title":"grasp: a simple protocol for decentralized git","url":"https://gitgrasp.com/","score":23,"flags":0,"comment_count":15,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"fiatjaf","user_is_author":true,"tags":["distributed","vcs"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ual4t5","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ual4t5/grasp_simple_protocol_for_decentralized"},{"short_id":"5r04ck","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:19:29.000-05:00","title":"LixCon 2026","url":"https://media.ccc.de/c/lixcon2026","score":20,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchonborn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["event","nix","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5r04ck","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5r04ck/lixcon_2026"},{"short_id":"prquts","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:30:49.000-05:00","title":"Emacs is my browser","url":"https://joshblais.com/blog/emacs-as-my-browser/","score":20,"flags":0,"comment_count":12,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"confusedalex","user_is_author":false,"tags":["emacs"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/prquts","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/prquts/emacs_is_my_browser"}]